        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:57PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 656 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fairview In Union County, or 10 miles north of Monroe, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Plyler, Locust, Norwood, Oakboro, Stanfield, Finger, and
Lake Tillery.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
